create a simple React app:

npx create-react-app react-docker-demo
cd react-docker-demo

2Ô∏è‚É£ Create .dockerignore

Create a file named .dockerignore in the project root to exclude unnecessary files:

node_modules
build
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
.git
.gitignore
README.md
npm-debug.log

3Ô∏è‚É£ Create the Multi-Stage Dockerfile

Create a file named Dockerfile in the root directory:

# ---- Stage 1: Build the React app ----
FROM node:18-alpine AS build

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy package files and install dependencies
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

# Copy source code and build the app
COPY . .
RUN npm run build

# ---- Stage 2: Serve app with Nginx ----
FROM nginx:stable-alpine

# Copy build output to Nginx HTML directory
COPY --from=build /app/build /usr/share/nginx/html

# Expose port 80
EXPOSE 80

# Start Nginx server
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

4Ô∏è‚É£ Build and Run the Docker Image

Build the image:

docker build -t react-docker-demo .


Run the container:

docker run -p 80:80 react-docker-demo


Then open http://localhost
 in your browser ‚Äî your React app should load üéâ

